POLOKWANE – Good news this week comes in the form of warmer weather in the city. People’s Weather’s forecast suggests mild to warm temperatures in Polokwane with highs of up to 24ºC expected.  Warmer temperatures will be welcomed by many following bitterly cold conditions and thunderstorms experienced over the past weekend. Read more: Cut-off low to bring “bitterly cold conditions” this weekend While the week will start off with a high of 18ºC today, warmer and sunny conditions will persist for the rest of the week with temperatures ranging from 22ºC to 24ºC. No rain has been forecast with only a 10% chance of rain expected today (May 23). 